title: Wind Speed Probabilities, .1 Degree 34 Knot, 120 Hour, NHS 2009
name: Wind Speed Probabilities, .1 Degree 34 Knot, 120 Hour, NHS 2009
description: The 34 knot, 120 hour cumulative wind speed probabilities show probabilities of sutained (1-minute average) surface (10-meter altitude) wind speeds equal to or exceeding 34 kt...39 mph (tropical storm force) at a regulary spaced (1/2 degree) grid of points. The cumulative periods begin at the start ofthe forecast period and extend through the entire 5-day forecat period from 0-120 hours. This shapefile was created by interpolating the requlary spaced 1/2 detree grid of points into a regularly spaced 1/10 degree grid of points. The 1/10 degree grid was furthur interpolated with a program named degrid (http://www.weather.gov/mdl/NDFD_GRIB2Decoder/) to create polygons which represented areas of 34 knot, 120 hour cumulative wind speed probabilities. These data are intended for geographic display and analysis at the national level and for large regional areas. The data should be displayed and analyzed at scales appropriate for 1:2,000,000-scale data. No responsibility is assumed by the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration in the use of these data.
